  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat </p>\n<p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>\n<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>sliced leeks</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>cavolo nero</strong>, discard the tough inner stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up &amp; slice into thin strips</p>\n<p>Dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1] </span><strong>Knorr </strong><strong>vegetable stock cube<span style=\"color:#e86754;\"> </span></strong>and the <strong>green tomato chutney</strong> in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>soup base</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the leeks have softened, add <strong>2/3 chopped garlic </strong>(save the rest for later!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>\n<p>Once fragrant, add the<strong> sliced cavolo nero</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> soup base</strong> and <strong>macaroni </strong>and cook, covered, for 6-8 min or until the cavolo nero has wilted and the macaroni is cooked with a slight bite – this is your <strong>Tuscan</strong> <strong>minestrone</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>ciabatta roll<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into 6 slices</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>ciabatta slices</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the ciabatta slices are cooking, strip the <strong>basil leaves</strong> from their stalks and chop them roughly, discarding the stalks</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2086.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the <strong>chopped basil</strong> and <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>(don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong> to form a smooth paste</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>juice</strong> of the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (use half if you don't love the taste of lemon!) and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>lemon &amp; basil salsa</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar, blitz in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
